  "closed_at": "2016-09-07T09:54:09Z",
  "body": "As described in the [doc](http://alibaba.github.io/weex/doc/references/component-defs.html), Weex provide three lifecycle options: `init`, `created`, `ready`. But I need `destroyed` hook function when component was destroyed to do some cleanup work to prevent memory leak.\n\n```\nmodule.exports = {\n  data: ...,\n  methods: ...,\n  destroyed: function () {\n    console.log('this component was destroyed.')\n  },\n  ...\n}\n```\n",
